The paper focuses on developing a service robot platform for daily assistance, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed strategy involves integrating a 3D object detection pipeline with a manipulation planner, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions optimizing the planner for kinematics, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the system is evaluated in a real-world environment setup, which involves system integration and control (cs.SY).
